# load in the Adjusted Close Price of three travel agencies
data = read.csv('~/Desktop/560/560-website/data_scource/stock_price_data/Adj.Close.csv')
data$Date = as.Date(data$Date, "%m/%d/%y")
head(data)
##     ABNB    BKNG   EXPE       Date
## 1 139.25 2104.87 130.47 2020-12-11
## 2 130.00 2089.21 123.02 2020-12-14
## 3 124.80 2066.01 123.33 2020-12-15
## 4 137.99 2098.05 126.00 2020-12-16
## 5 147.05 2098.71 124.98 2020-12-17
## 6 157.30 2113.43 124.48 2020-12-18
#timeseries
ts_abnb = ts(data$ABNB)
ts_bkng = ts(data$BKNG)
ts_expe = ts(data$EXPE)
#returns
return_abnb = diff(log(ts_abnb))
return_bkng = diff(log(ts_bkng))
return_expe = diff(log(ts_expe))

check stationary

par(mfrow=c(3,1))
plot(return_abnb, ylab = "Return", main = "ABNB Return", col = "dark green")
plot(return_bkng, ylab = "Return", main = "BKNG Return", col = "orange")
plot(return_expe, ylab = "Return", main = "EXPE Return", col = "red")

#The return plots of three companies all showed that volatility is not constant.
#ACF plots
par(mfrow=c(3,1))
acf(return_abnb, main = "ACF of ABNB Return", col = "dark green")
acf(return_bkng, main = "ACF of BKNG Return", col = "orange")
acf(return_expe, main = "ACF of EXPE Return", col = "red")

#The acf plots show that the return is stationary.
#PACF plots
par(mfrow=c(3,1))
pacf(return_abnb, main = "PACF of ABNB Return", col = "dark green") # p = 10
pacf(return_bkng, main = "PACF of BKNG Return", col = "orange") # p = 4, 14, 17
pacf(return_expe, main = "PACF of EXPE Return", col = "red")

#adf-test
adf.test(return_abnb) # p-value = 0.01
## Warning in adf.test(return_abnb): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  return_abnb
## Dickey-Fuller = -6.8523, Lag order = 6, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
adf.test(return_bkng) # p-value = 0.01
## Warning in adf.test(return_bkng): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  return_bkng
## Dickey-Fuller = -7.3853, Lag order = 6, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
adf.test(return_expe) # p-value = 0.01
## Warning in adf.test(return_expe): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  return_expe
## Dickey-Fuller = -6.7589, Lag order = 6, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
# The p-value is smaller than significant level 0.05, so we can reject the null hypothesis and have enough evidence to conclude that the return of these three companies are stationary.

ARCH

# Fit timeseries into proper ARIMA model
auto.arima(ts_abnb) # ARIMA (0,1,0)
## Series: ts_abnb 
## ARIMA(0,1,0) 
## 
## sigma^2 = 33.67:  log likelihood = -943.64
## AIC=1889.27   AICc=1889.29   BIC=1892.97
auto.arima(ts_bkng) # ARIMA (0,1,0)
## Series: ts_bkng 
## ARIMA(0,1,0) 
## 
## sigma^2 = 2142:  log likelihood = -1560.36
## AIC=3122.72   AICc=3122.73   BIC=3126.41
auto.arima(ts_expe) # ARIMA (1,1,0)
## Series: ts_expe 
## ARIMA(1,1,0) 
## 
## Coefficients:
##           ar1
##       -0.0122
## s.e.   0.0596
## 
## sigma^2 = 16.58:  log likelihood = -837.95
## AIC=1679.91   AICc=1679.95   BIC=1687.29
abnb_arima = Arima(ts_abnb, order = c(0,1,0))
bkng_arima = Arima(ts_bkng, order = c(0,1,0))
expe_arima = Arima(ts_expe, order = c(1,1,0))

# Get residual from Arima models
abnb_residue = residuals(abnb_arima)
bkng_residue = residuals(bkng_arima)
expe_residue = residuals(expe_arima)
#ARCH test on residual
library(FinTS)
## 
## Attaching package: 'FinTS'
## The following object is masked from 'package:forecast':
## 
##     Acf
ArchTestRes = c(
  as.character(ArchTest(abnb_residue)$p.value),
  as.character(ArchTest(bkng_residue)$p.value),
  as.character(ArchTest(expe_residue)$p.value))
names(ArchTestRes) <- c("ABNB", "BKNG", "EXPE")
ArchTestRes # p value of ARCH test on residual
##                   ABNB                   BKNG                   EXPE 
## "2.02357536457396e-05"    "0.598107849687107"    "0.960732203119352"
#squared residual
colors<-c("#B4EEB4",'orange','#FFC1C1')
title <-c("ABNB","BKNG","EXPE")
residual = list(ABNB=abnb_residue, BKNG=bkng_residue, EXPE=expe_residue)
for (i in 1:3) {
  theme<-theme(panel.background=element_rect(fill=colors[i]))
  p1<-autoplot((residual[[i]])^2)+theme+labs(y='Squared Residual')
  p2<-ggAcf((residual[[i]])^2)+theme+labs(title='')
  p3<-ggPacf((residual[[i]])^2)+theme+labs(title='')
  grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3,nrow=3)
}

model_abnb <- list()
temp <- data.frame()
ls_abnb <- matrix(rep(NA, 2*16), nrow = 16)
cc<-1
for (p in 1:4) {
  for (q in 1:4) {
    model_abnb[[cc]] <- garch(return_abnb, order = c(q,p), trace=F)
    ls_abnb[cc,] <- c(p,q)
    print(c(p,q))
    cc<-cc+1
  }
}
